reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Seller doesn't know their own product. Makes claims all the install videos claim are not possible.
reviews.reviewText: Seller states in their handbook that if you use it as a repeater, that it will use half the bandwidth UNLESS you receive on one channel (5GHz) and repeat on anther (2.4GHz). This is on the last page of the little booklet. I've asked the seller multiple times for specific instructions on how to do this setup and each time, they've come back with "it's magic" - just follow the connection and it will magically happen. All the installation videos show the same signal being repeated - not the alternate channel. There is no clarity on whether the alternate channel needs to have the same SSID. I've asked for a step-by-step set of instructions over and over and I keep getting the same kind of responses. See below - this is the exact opposite of what is demonstrated in all the installation videos - the SSID of the signal connected is the signal relayed: "According to the reply from the technical department.Plug in the repeater, and then expand the 5G SSID. Then a 5G and a 2.4G wifi will be expanded, and then you can connect them separately.This is the principle of operation, there is only one path."
